<TITLE> Speeding bus kills mother, child at Kakrail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 27 (bdnews24.com)A mother and child were killed as a recklessly speeding bus ploughed into their rickshaw at the city's busy Kakrail intersection on Friday, said police. Reshma Akter, 45, and her six-year old daughter were travelling in the rickshaw when a Probhatee Poribahan bus ran into it at around 9:30am, killing the mother on the spot, said Ramna police station sub-inspector Abdul Quddus. He told bdnews24.com the critically injured child was rushed to Dhaka Medical College Hospital, where she succumbed to her injuries. Police held the bus driver, identified as 'Wahid', said the SI. Reshma, originally from Kamargaon in Khulna, lived in a rented apartment at Rampura. The two dead bodies were being kept at the DMCH morgue, said Quddus. bd
